<chapter id="installing" xreflabel="Installing">
<title>Installing the Openbabel roll</title>

<section id="requirements" xreflabel="Requirements">
<title>Rocks Version</title>

<para>
The Openbabel Roll is for use with Rocks version &document-version;.
The Babel Roll is does not require any other rolls.
Compatiblity has been verified with the following rolls:
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>AutoClickChem</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>

</section>

&source-roll-installing-standard;

<section id="installing-running-server" xreflabel="On an existing server">
<title>Adding roll to the existing server</title>
<para>
The Openbabel roll can be added to an existing server (frontend).
Assume that you have an ISO image of the roll called babel.iso.
The following procedure will install the roll:
<screen>
# rocks add roll babel.iso
# rocks enable roll babel
# cd /export/rocks/install
# rocks create distro
# rocks run roll babel | /bin/sh
</screen>
</para>
</section>

<section id="installing-nodes" xreflabel="Adding the roll to the nodes">
<title>Adding the roll to the nodes</title>

<para>
To add the the Openbabel roll to the nodes of your cluster, you'll
need to reinstall the nodes.
</para>

<para>
To reinstall all your nodes, as root execute:
</para>

<para>
<screen>
# rocks set host compute boot action=install
# rocks run host compute command=reboot
</screen>
</para>

</section>

</chapter>
